%YAML 1.1
%TAG !u! tag:unity3d.com,2011:
--- !u!114 &11400000
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 9e7c527a6f66a8c49a6fab10a94681fc, type: 3}
  m_Name: Day3MorningP
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  sequenceId: albert_day3_morning_pill
  lines:
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "There\u2019s going to be a slight shift in plans today. Two fuse boxes
      broke last night at the infirmary."
    sendDelay: 0
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 1
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: However, I have full confidence in your abilities to fix them and get optimal
      power flowing for that quadrant again.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "Sounds good to me. A few broken fuse boxes aren\u2019t an issue
        for me."
      nextLineIndex: 2
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: "How annoying\u2026 but I have no other choice. I\u2019ll get it
        done."
      nextLineIndex: 3
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "That\u2019s the spirit. Just keep on with keeping DOLOS happy, and everything
      will be ok."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "You\u2019re right. You don\u2019t."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 4
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Get the job done, and keep DOLOS pleased. It\u2019s in your best interest."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Wear and tear is the most likely answer. I assume some of the older technicians
      didn\u2019t do the proper job of insulating the wires properly."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 6
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "But\u2026 that\u2019s why they\u2019re not on the SUNSET16 anymore."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 7
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "DOLOS doesn\u2019t tolerate failure. So be sure you complete this task
      efficiently."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Regardless of your adjusted schedule for the day, I have some time to burn
      before I start my rounds at the nuclear core. Got any questions for me?
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices:
    - choiceText: In what way does the DOLOS Corporation determine what makes a good
        employee when screening potential employees?
      nextLineIndex: 9
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: "How\u2019s the nuclear core these days?"
      nextLineIndex: 17
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: Heard NUSA Electric filed for bankruptcy recently.
      nextLineIndex: 23
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: I have no more questions. Message me tonight once I get those fuse
        boxes repaired.
      nextLineIndex: 33
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 1
    advanceToLine: 32
    repeat: 1
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Thinking back about how your screening went, I reckon?
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: You could say that, yeah. The process was a ride to say the least.
      nextLineIndex: 10
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: I was thinking about what your screening was like.
      nextLineIndex: 14
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: They had to meet the very specific criteria the DOLOS Corporation was looking
      for.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 11
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Since the SUNSET16 was an isolated environment, candidates with familial
      connections or other relationships weren\u2019t the most ideal for the position. "
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 12
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Of course, having a solid technical background was also a major factor
      in hiring, which you and I both had.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 13
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: So, as long as your profile matched what the corporation was looking for,
      you were selected for the job.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: albert_interview
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "That was some time ago. I\u2019m sure the process was the same as yours."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 15
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: The standard background checks were asked, followed by questions to filter
      out ideal candidates who could work in an environment like the SUNSET16.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 16
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: As long as the candidate met the very specific requirements, they were
      hired.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: albert_interview
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Smooth sailing as usual. The graphs are flat, and the readings are stable.
      Boring, but that\u2019s the goal."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 18
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "There was a time when the core was\u2026 malfunctioning."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: Really? How so?
      nextLineIndex: 19
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: "Well\u2026 a malfunction is something that you could handle."
      nextLineIndex: 21
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: The cooling system was starting to fail. You could thank a virus being
      uploaded by a foreign corporation for that.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 20
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Worked my magic with some other technicians in other parts of the ship,
      and turned things around. That\u2019s why they hired me."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "That\u2019s for certain. It\u2019s part of the job package."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 22
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: The DOLOS Corporation expected good results from me, and I provided them.
      They expect equally promising results from you.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "They made some\u2026 poor financial decisions in tandem with being attacked
      by a rival competitor."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 24
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: The company ran out of money by the end of that conflict. Shelled out the
      rest of their assets.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: What happened to the NUSA CEO then? After the bankruptcy scandal?
      nextLineIndex: 25
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Last I heard, she had connections in China. After that, I don\u2019t know
      much. The rest of the shareholders scattered to other conglomerates in North
      America and Europe."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 26
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Why\u2019d you ask?"
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: No reason. Just passing time.
      nextLineIndex: 27
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    - choiceText: Could the same happen here?
      nextLineIndex: 28
      offPillChoice: 0
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Uh huh\u2026"
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "DOLOS is different. More structured than other mega corporations. We\u2019re
      not going anywhere. And neither are you."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.01
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 8
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: Brushing up on old files?
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: Something like that.
      nextLineIndex: 30
      offPillChoice: 1
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: They were an early program, before the Aegis Collars were designed. It
      was actually the results of that program that led to their development.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 31
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: After each major shift, it was company protocol to hook up to a terminal
      and watch a series of lights and sound effects.
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0.5
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: 32
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "What we have now with the capsules is significantly more streamlined in
      boosting productivity and providing other benefits. That\u2019s why it\u2019s
      important to take your capsule shots every day."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 1
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices:
    - choiceText: "Right\u2026 yeah, of course."
      nextLineIndex: 8
      offPillChoice: 1
      showOnRepeat: 0
    advanceToLine: 0
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
  - speakerName: Albert
    portrait: {fileID: 0}
    text: "Alright, I\u2019ll catch you later then."
    sendDelay: 1
    delayRepeats: 0
    autoAdvanceDelay: 0
    choices: []
    advanceToLine: -1
    repeat: 0
    repeated: 0
    loreEntry: 
    switchToDOLOS: 0
